= Finance & Compliance =

{{info}}
This page now provides only the public-facing summary.
Detailed finance/compliance working material moved to the internal repository on **29 April 2026**.
{{/info}}

== 1. Public Summary ==

FactHarbor's finance and compliance posture is guided by:

* transparency about major funding and expenses
* independence from donor influence
* mission-locked nonprofit use of funds
* auditable internal controls for sensitive transactions

== 2. What Remains Public ==

Public-facing policy and governance pages remain here:

* [[Legal Framework>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Legal Framework.WebHome]]
* [[Transparency Policy>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Transparency-Policy]]
* [[Large Donations Policy>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Large Donations Policy.WebHome]]
* [[Reimbursable Expense Report>>FactHarbor.Organisation.Legal and Compliance.Reimbursable Expenses.WebHome]]

== 3. What Moved Private ==

The detailed working material was moved out of the public repo tip because it can contain:

* banking-status and account-opening workflow details
* registration and tax-filing progress
* internal finance/compliance operational notes
* other admin-sensitive legal-financial context

Private canonical location:

* `robertschaub/FactHarbor-internal`
